Metadata: Importance of pre-recruitment life-history stages to population dynamics of the woolly sculpin "Clinocottus analis."

Using cohort analysis and matrix population modeling, the authors examined the relative influence of pre- versus post-â€‹recruitment life-history events on population size of a temperate intertidal fish, "Clinocottus analis." The goal was to determine which life-history stage was most responsible for temporal changes in population size from 1996 to 2000 at 2 sites in San Diego, California, both seasonally and during the 1997-98 El Nino Southern Oscillation.
